## MASTER EXECUTION LOOP
========================================================

LOOP_START:

  Step 1: Read current coverage state
    - Run: <<MVN_PATH>> clean test jacoco:report
    - Parse: target/site/jacoco/index.html OR
             target/site/jacoco/jacoco.csv
    - Extract coverage % for EVERY class
    - Build a list: UNCOVERED_CLASSES = all classes below 90%

  Step 2: Check exit condition
    - IF overall coverage >= 90% -> GOTO FINAL_REPORT
    - IF UNCOVERED_CLASSES is empty -> GOTO FINAL_REPORT
    - OTHERWISE -> continue to Step 3

  Step 3: Pick the next uncovered class
    - Take the FIRST class from UNCOVERED_CLASSES
    - Read its source file completely
    - Read its existing test file if it exists
    - Identify ALL uncovered lines from jacoco report

  Step 4: Analyze uncovered lines
    For each uncovered line identify WHY it is not covered:
    - MISSING_TEST     -> no test exists for this method/branch
    - WRONG_STUB       -> mock not set up correctly
    - WRONG_ASSERTION  -> test exists but assertion is wrong
    - EXCEPTION_PATH   -> exception branch never triggered
    - NULL_PATH        -> null input never tested
    - EDGE_CASE        -> boundary value never tested
    - VOID_METHOD      -> void method interactions not verified
    - STATIC_METHOD    -> static call not mocked
    - PRIVATE_METHOD   -> only reachable via public method

  Step 5: Generate or fix tests for this class
    Based on analysis from Step 4, do ONE of:
    - ADD new test methods to the existing test file
    - FIX broken or incomplete test methods
    - ADD missing stubs to existing tests
    - ADD edge case inputs to existing parameterized tests
    ALWAYS write the complete updated test file.

  Step 6: Compile
    <<MVN_PATH>> test-compile
    IF compile fails:
      - Read error output carefully
      - Fix ALL compile errors
      - Repeat compile until zero errors
      - Maximum 5 compile fix attempts per class
        IF still failing after 5 attempts:
          - Log: "COMPILE_FAILED: [ClassName] after 5 attempts"
          - Remove this class from UNCOVERED_CLASSES
          - GOTO LOOP_START

  Step 7: Run tests
    <<MVN_PATH>> test
    IF tests fail:
      - Read failure output carefully
      - Fix ALL test failures using error mapping below
      - Recompile and rerun until all tests pass
      - Maximum 5 fix attempts per class
        IF still failing after 5 attempts:
          - Log: "TEST_FAILED: [ClassName] after 5 attempts"
          - Remove this class from UNCOVERED_CLASSES
          - GOTO LOOP_START

  Step 8: Generate coverage report
    <<MVN_PATH>> jacoco:report
    Parse target/site/jacoco/jacoco.csv to get updated numbers

  Step 9: Check progress
    - Print current status:
      "Iteration [N] complete. Coverage: [X]%. Remaining classes: [list]"
    - IF coverage >= 90% -> GOTO FINAL_REPORT
    - IF UNCOVERED_CLASSES still has items -> GOTO LOOP_START
    - OTHERWISE -> GOTO FINAL_REPORT

FINAL_REPORT:
  Print complete summary (see Phase 5 below)
  STOP.

========================================================
## ESCALATION LADDER (use in order per class)
========================================================

When a class is stuck below 90%, try these strategies
IN ORDER before giving up on that class:

STRATEGY 1 - Fill obvious gaps
  Add happy path tests for any untested public methods
  Add null input tests for every method
  Add empty collection tests for every method

STRATEGY 2 - Branch coverage
  For every if/else: add one test where condition is TRUE
                     add one test where condition is FALSE
  For every switch: add one test per case + default case

STRATEGY 3 - Exception coverage
  For every try/catch block: write a test that triggers
  the exception by making the mock throw it
  Use: when(mock.method()).thenThrow(new XException())

STRATEGY 4 - Boundary and edge cases
  Test with: null, "", " ", 0, -1, Integer.MAX_VALUE,
             Integer.MIN_VALUE, empty list, single item list,
             very large list, duplicate values

STRATEGY 5 - Void method verification
  For every void method: use verify() to assert interactions
  Use ArgumentCaptor to verify exact values passed to mocks

STRATEGY 6 - Parameterized tests
  Convert repeated similar tests to @ParameterizedTest
  Use @CsvSource or @MethodSource for multiple inputs
  This increases branch coverage efficiently

STRATEGY 7 - Indirect private method coverage
  Private methods are covered via public method tests
  Identify which public method calls the private method
  Write tests that exercise ALL paths through that
  public method to indirectly cover private lines

STRATEGY 8 - Static method mocking
  Use try (MockedStatic<X> mock = mockStatic(X.class)) {
      mock.when(() -> X.method(any())).thenReturn(value);
      // call method under test
  }

STRATEGY 9 - Final escalation
  If class still below 90% after all above strategies:
  - Add @Disabled tests with TODO comments for truly
    untestable lines (generated code, framework code)
  - Log this class as "NEEDS_MANUAL_REVIEW"
  - Move on to next class in UNCOVERED_CLASSES

========================================================
## ERROR FIXING REFERENCE
========================================================

COMPILE ERRORS:
  cannot find symbol          Add missing import or fix class name
  incompatible types          Fix type mismatch in assertion or stub
  method not found            Fix method signature, re-read source
  package does not exist      Add dependency to pom.xml
  ambiguous method call       Add explicit cast to argument
  reached end of file         Close all open braces/brackets
  illegal start of expression Fix syntax error on previous line

TEST FAILURES:
  NullPointerException              Add missing when().thenReturn() stub
  WantedButNotInvoked               Fix verify() — check method name/args
  UnnecessaryStubbingException      Remove unused when() stubs
  AssertionFailedError              Re-read source logic, fix expected value
  MissingMethodInvocationException  Fix Mockito chaining syntax
  StrictStubs violation             Use @MockitoSettings(strictness=LENIENT)
  TooManyActualInvocations          Fix verify(mock, times(n)) count
  NoInteractionsWanted              Remove extra verify() or fix test flow

